cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NA 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with tumor segmentation in histology images using deep convolutional features. The use of persistent homology also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The efficient computation of topological persistence could also place it in the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the use of algebraic tools from homology theory suggests that it could belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
